one over at Verant. <br><br>We are in the game not to deal the most damage nor do any fancy feign pulling or buffing. But to hold aggro and take a good beating if your the MT and to provide support damage if your not. <br><br>It's too hard to taunt, thats it. Relying on weapon procs is not a plan but a cover up. It's a loophole on how to become better at something (taunt) that we should already be great at. <br><br>Taunt is a half ass skill at best, talking to numerous 50+ warriors it doesn't get any better later on. In fact it just gets worse. <br><br>I don't see how anyone could say it would be unbalancing for our taunt to be better. Shadowknights could out taunt us hands down with a click of a button (disease cloud). I won't even mention Paladins, or Rangers. Lets not forget monks who don't even have a mean of taunting besides pure damage. <br><br>Like I said I am not here to become a flame sponge, I am just posting wondering YOUR thoughts on this. Your thoughts on our taunting ability. If you think we should recieve an upgrade or change. <br><br>Some Idea's I have pondered are...<br><br>~ An upgrade in skill and success of Warrior only taunt. <br><br>~ A taunt discipline, something with a low refresh time and upgraded maybe 3- 4 times throughout your life. For example...<br><br>Level 20 - Discipline of the (whatever) <br><br>This discipline would add X amount of hate. <br><br>Duration - Instant<br><br>Refresh - 4 Minutes (which would decrese with level)<br><br>Then another taunt discipline at (example) 30, 50 then finally at 60. <br><br><br>Well I have rambled long enough, please post your thoughts and try to keep it flame free. <br><br><br>Windance Warwillow<br>30th Warrior <br>Brell Serilis<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaabidano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aabidano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 9:22:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> Taunt as it stands isn't broken IMO.  Or even in need of a fix.  It's up to other classes to manage their own agro.  Properly played, it's resonably easy to hold agro.  Also, almost every non-tanking class has a means to reduce their own agro.<br><br>If rogues, monks, and wizards over agro , they are going to take a beating for it.  That's one of the seperators in between good ones and bad ones.  Once they die a few dozen times due to it most figure it out.  Even moreso with Enchanters, though they can't always help it.<br><br>Procs on weapons just mean more damage can be safely dealt by other classes without undue agro.<br><br>Just my 2cp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uroehm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roehm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 375<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 10:00:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> Taunt works.<br><br>There is a warrior taunt ability, however it is a 55+ class skill AOE Taunt. Have fun aaxp'ing.<br><br>It is incumbent on other classes that get on a mobs hate list to keep themselves low enough on the list to not catch any aggro (rogues who don't have an Evade macro in their backstab key, overnuking wizards, etc).<br><br>It is also incumbent on warriors to understand how weapon speed, procs, and damage all affect their aggro status and to use that to move themselves up or down the list accordingly.<br><br>Also taunt is very level dependant. So level up and mash that taunt key. <br><br>It does work, well works everywhere except Cazic Thule <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9966>Roehm Ironwolf</a><BR>Warlord of the Tribunal<BR><a href=http://www.bladesofwrath.com>Blades of Wrath</a><BR><a href=http://www.torvonnilous.net>Torvonnilous</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 10:08:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> As it stands today, a competent warrior must be grouped with other players who are also competent for taunt to work properly.  As a 60 warrior I have little to no problem holding taunt unless the players I am with are marginal or worse.  This is for regular experience grouping.  And I don't have the best agro holding weapons (ornate blade of the general main hand and sword of morning off hand).<br><br>Now, this doesn't address tanking the big mobs.  Taunt there does seem a little buggy at times.  Basically it requires everyone to be doing their job pretty much exactly right for it to work the way it ought.  And strangely enough, it seems getting 30 or 40 people together who understand what their jobs are and can do them competently can sometimes be a real strain, at least for my guild.<br><br>I guess my thoughts boil down to this.  If everyone is on the ball and doing what they should, taunt works great as it is today.  If not, then its a problem.  Why should Verant be responsible for making it easier to succeed with sloppy play and a lack of class competency?<br><br><br><br>   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushadokastr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>shadokastr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 10:44:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> I have felt since L20 that the ability to do our job (take and keep aggro) is what makes warriors so cool.  Its a challange to keep aggro.  I like that challange.  It can be a pain when your shammy is always getting agro and then running away, so educate them.  If your guild can't figure it out, educate them or find a better guild.  When everyone works together to do something cool, it feels much better than just standing there hitting kick once in a while.  Leave the challange, revel in it, enjoy it, and scream at your groups and guild if you have to.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   This game is all about people working together.  and when people work together, aggro isn't a problem (most of the time)<br><br><br><br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=146119"><img src="http://www.logicfactor.com/spinfire/Nevsig.jpg" border=0></a><br>click sig for profile</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwindenwarmheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winden Warmheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 10:46:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Im not...</span><hr size=1> I am not in any means condoning sloppy play. If I can't hold aggro because of someone over nuking or whatever and they croak because of it thats their problem.<br><br>But what im saying is, when @#%$ hits the fan and you need to get a taunt in or someone is gonna croak, a SK or Paladin even a ranger could grab the aggro quicker then we would beable too. <br><br>From people's experience it would seem taunt rarely even works, like something 1 in 3 or 4 attempts? Thats crazy. <br><br>I'm not looking for a level of aggro that would ruin the gameplay and strategy aspects of a group. I'm simply looking for a little increase in the effectiveness and stability of taunt. <br><br>Perhaps a long refresh (30 - 60 mins?) taunt which when crap does go wrong mash it and you grab aggro. The refresh would be long on that ability but it would be a very usefull situational ability. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiskandaralazeem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 11:01:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.purgatory.net/alex/medion.jpg width=64 height=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Im not...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Perhaps a long refresh (30 - 60 mins?) taunt which when crap does go wrong mash it and you grab aggro. The refresh would be long on that ability but it would be a very usefull situational ability.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>Someone already answered your question. =) It's called Area Taunt. It's a warrior-only alternate advancement class ability. Minimum AA cost to get AE taunt is 23 points. True, you will have to work to get it, but most warriors agree that the cost is well worth the reward.<br><br>I do understand your frustration. I assume you group for exp most of the time, without doing a lot of raiding. Trust me, if you ever get the chance to raid at high levels, you'll see how powerful warriors really can be. We're solid in exp groups, but we shine on raids. <p><html><body><p style="font-size:110%"><b><a href="http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Iskandar" STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Veteran Iskandar Alazeem</a><br><a href=http://www.steelwarrior.org STYLE="text-decoration: none" target="_blank">Steel Warrior</a> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">moderator</a><br><a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Keepers of the Faith</a></b></p></body></html></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiskandaralazeem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskandar Alazeem</A> at: 4/12/02 11:10:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1234<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 11:12:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Im not...</span><hr size=1> in all seriousness; if they made the game again where warriors could hit taunt and instantly grab all kinds of aggro i'm sure the other classes would see it as &quot; unbalanced&quot; and detrimental to &quot; we suck no one will group us up they only need war/clr/ench for groups &quot;.<br><br>Taunt could use a little tweaking we all could agree on for the most part; but to beef it up to the point where it's 100% reliable and taking no effort from anyone else would make everyone elses job pretty much non-existant.<br><br>Tant sometimes takes creativity and even dumb luck. when you got the people around you that know <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> as the warrior should be the one sponging all the hits; than it rarely; if ever; becomes a concern. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwindenwarmheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winden Warmheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 11:12:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  I know of...</span><hr size=1> I know of area taunt.... <br><br>But it happens a little late don't ya think??? Unless none of you need to hold aggro of multiple or single mobs from level 1 - 58... <br><br>Cause we all know how we never ever need to grab aggro RIGHT now before level 59... /sigh<br><br>Listen, other hybrids classes can grab aggro RIGHT Now without any advancement skill, Let alone one so costly (though im sure it will be worth the cost). I suggested a lower level discipline taunt, not a replacement for the 59 AoE taunt.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 11:53:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> AoE taunt coming that late is no worse than pet classes finally controlling their pets at the same level.<br><br>The main purpose of a warrior it seems it to get beat on and shrug it off so the other less fortunate classes can live fighting the big mobs. Watching agro is everyones job, not just ours, although we do seem to try the hardest at times.<br><br>Imo the only thing to change on the warrior class would be setting  our mitigation tables on par with a monks avoidance tables ( which would make us close to invincible <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) but that is another argument for later. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a><BR> 53rd Human Champion of the Eternal Bloodguard <BR>Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrettsc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>brettsc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 2:05:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> In most situations, having the mob hitting the warrior is the best thing for everyone involved.<br><br>If taunt *always* (within reason) worked, the whole aspect of this part of the game would be trivialised.<br><br>So it requires some work from everyone involved. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udracillionofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DracillionofQeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 7:11:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why??? (Taunt Related)</span><hr size=1> Area taunt is a level 59 class ability.<br><br>I agree with you about taunt.  Warriors have complained about this for a LONG time.  When Verant still had their official class boards up, it was the most common complaint.  And a couple of years ago, when they were doing class balancing and soliciting information from Warriors, it was one of the most commonly ask for skill fixes.  So maybe we didn't have a formal petition, but VI heard and probably still hears us load and clear.<br><br>Their answer was Area Taunt.  Great skill if your 59+ and get to that AA point.  Until the, you have to rely on haste, good weapons, and your group controlling its aggro.  Its absolutely beyond me to understand why VI would make us the best tank there is but yet make us one of the poorest taunting and aggro generating classes.   <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127089">Dracillion of Qeynos</a><BR>Warlord of Omani<BR>Bertoxxulous Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwindenwarmheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winden Warmheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 8:06:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Not looking for...</span><hr size=1> I never asked for taunt to work always ALWAYS with no fail on a regular bases. <br><br>I just said that other melee classes can pull aggro better then we can, I would like us to beable to pull aggro as easy as they can. <br><br>The other idea's were &quot;oh crap&quot; situations... a 40 - 60 minute refresh top of the hate list taunt (before the level 59 aoe one). That would be nice to have. <br><br>People are saying its unbalancing for taunt to be upgraded. But shadowknights/paladins already are able to out taunt us (fast aggro) easily via a spells/taunt mix.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 867<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 8:47:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=660.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Not looking for...</span><hr size=1> i cant decide if i would rather have a single taunt that works like area taunt.... or have area taunt.<br><br>i was deathly afraid id hit the wrong key in ring of fire last night, but it is a lifesaver other times<br>(i hate ring of fire more than any other thing in the entire game, just for the record) <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubelwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>belwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 9:00:14 pm)</font><br>