pons and armor, searching for that next thing that'll give me the little bit of an edge I might need.<br><br>&quot;Give us something that we can use as a last ditch bailout&quot;...use your head so you don't need a last ditch bailout.   @#%$ happens...when it does, you have to deal with it.  If it was because of a mistake, learn from the mistake, you become a better player that way.  If it was bad luck, accept it, after all...@#%$ happens.  Want something similar to AoE taunt?  Work your ass off to level 59, and earn it.<br><br>&quot;The druids are whining and might become better because of it, why shouldn't we?&quot;  Well, for one, it's generally accepted that Druids have relatively little use at highend raids, except a couple buffs and the ability to get people there quickly.  Secondly, you're a warrior...I see the warriors of EQ as being a fairly no-nonsense group of people...people who aren't inclined to whining, griping, complaining, etc.  So we've chosen a class that may have a couple faults.  We deal with it, silently, and still manage to be successful, effective players.  In chosing a class with our given ability set, we've accepted a challenge...the challenge to make the most of what we have, and to succeed at whatever levels of the game we persue.<br><br>I like challenges. <p><table width=350 height=120 border=1 style="border-color:#000000; border-width:3; border-style:solid;font-family:Arial;" cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td background="http://www.guardianalliance.org/gfx/gasig.jpg" style="border-style:none;">   <img src="http://www.guardianalliance.org/gfx/x.gif" width=30 align=left>   <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=200>      <tr>      <td>         <font color=#FFFFFF size=+1>         <b><center>         <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45412"          style="text-decoration:none; color: #ffffff;"><u>Thak Havocblade         </a>         </u>         </b><br></font